<span id="page_27">p. 27</span>

### LAMENT FOR ADONIS

<span class="smallcaps">Ah</span>, for Adonis!  
See, he is dying,  
Delicate, lovely,  
Slender Adonis.

Ah, for Adonis!  
Weep, O ye maidens,  
Beating your bosoms,  
Rending your tunics.

O Cytherea,  
Hasten, for never  
Loved thou another  
As thy Adonis.

See, on the rosy  
Cheek with its dimple,  
Blushing no longer,  
Thanatos’ shadow.

Save him, O Goddess!  
Thou, the beguiler,  
All-powerful, holy,  
Stay the dread evil.

Ah, for Adonis!  
No more at vintage  
Time will he come with  
Bloom of the meadows.

Ah, for Adonis!  
See, he is dying,  
Fading as flowers  
With the lost summer.

